📊 Audit Dashboard for Motorcycle Accessories Shop
Project Report
1. Introduction

In today’s retail environment, data-driven decision-making plays a crucial role in improving business performance. This project presents the development of an Audit Dashboard for a Motorcycle Accessories Shop, aimed at monitoring sales, inventory, and operational efficiency.

The dashboard provides a centralized platform to visualize key business metrics, enabling shop owners to make informed decisions quickly and effectively.

2. Objective

The main objectives of this project are:

To track sales and revenue in real-time
To monitor inventory levels and prevent stock shortages
To analyze product performance
To improve overall operational efficiency
To support data-driven decision-making
3. Scope of the Project

This dashboard is designed specifically for small to medium-scale motorcycle accessories shops. It focuses on:

Sales analysis
Inventory management
Product performance tracking
Trend visualization

The system can be extended further with advanced analytics and automation features.

4. System Overview

The Audit Dashboard integrates various data points into a single interface. It collects and processes data related to:

Daily sales transactions
Product stock levels
Supplier and purchase details

The processed data is then displayed in the form of charts, graphs, and summary metrics for easy understanding.

5. Key Features
📊 Sales Tracking: Displays daily, weekly, and monthly revenue
📦 Inventory Monitoring: Tracks stock levels and alerts for low inventory
🔍 Product Analysis: Identifies best-selling and slow-moving items
📈 Trend Visualization: Shows sales patterns and growth trends
⚡ User-Friendly Interface: Easy to navigate and interpret
